verses.text_plain: I will sing of the mercies of the Lord for ever: with my mouth will I make known thy faithfulness to all generations.
verses.verse_html:
1I will sing of the mercies of the Lord for ever: with my mouth will I make known thy faithfulness to all generations. ▼
▼ Maschil…: or, A Psalm for Ethan the Ezrahite, to give instruction
 , ▼
▼ to all…: Heb. to generation and generation

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Maschil…: or, A Psalm for Ethan the Ezrahite, to give instruction
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Maschil…: or, A Psalm for Ethan the Ezrahite, to give instruction

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to all…: Heb. to generation and generation
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to all…: Heb. to generation and generation

verses.text_plain: For I have said, Mercy shall be built up for ever: thy faithfulness shalt thou establish in the very heavens.
verses.verse_html: 2For I have said, Mercy shall be built up for ever: thy faithfulness shalt thou establish in the very heavens.

verses.text_plain: I have made a covenant with my chosen, I have sworn unto David my servant,
verses.verse_html: 3I have made a covenant with my chosen, I have sworn unto David my servant,

verses.text_plain: Thy seed will I establish for ever, and build up thy throne to all generations. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 4Thy seed will I establish for ever, and build up thy throne to all generations. Selah.

verses.text_plain: And the heavens shall praise thy wonders, O Lord: thy faithfulness also in the congregation of the saints.
verses.verse_html: 5And the heavens shall praise thy wonders, O Lord: thy faithfulness also in the congregation of the saints.

verses.text_plain: For who in the heaven can be compared unto the Lord? who among the sons of the mighty can be likened unto the Lord?
verses.verse_html: 6For who in the heaven can be compared unto the Lord? who among the sons of the mighty can be likened unto the Lord?

verses.text_plain: God is greatly to be feared in the assembly of the saints, and to be had in reverence of all them that are about him.
verses.verse_html: 7God is greatly to be feared in the assembly of the saints, and to be had in reverence of all them that are about him.

tokens.text: and to be had in reverence

verses.text_plain: O Lord God of hosts, who is a strong Lord like unto thee? or to thy faithfulness round about thee?
verses.verse_html: 8O Lord God of hosts, who is a strong Lord like unto thee? or to thy faithfulness round about thee?

tokens.text: like unto thee? or to thy faithfulness

verses.text_plain: Thou rulest the raging of the sea: when the waves thereof arise, thou stillest them.
verses.verse_html: 9Thou rulest the raging of the sea: when the waves thereof arise, thou stillest them.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast broken Rahab in pieces, as one that is slain; thou hast scattered thine enemies with thy strong arm.
verses.verse_html:
10Thou hast broken Rahab in pieces, as one that is slain; thou hast scattered thine enemies with thy strong arm. ▼
▼ Rahab: or, Egypt
 , ▼
▼ thy…: Heb. the arm of thy strength

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thy…: Heb. the arm of thy strength
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thy…: Heb. the arm of thy strength

verses.text_plain: The heavens are thine, the earth also is thine: as for the world and the fulness thereof, thou hast founded them.
verses.verse_html:
11The heavens are thine, the earth also is thine: as for the world and the fulness thereof, thou hast founded them. ▼
▼ the fulness…: or, all it containeth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the fulness…: or, all it containeth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the fulness…: or, all it containeth

verses.text_plain: The north and the south thou hast created them: Tabor and Hermon shall rejoice in thy name.
verses.verse_html: 12The north and the south thou hast created them: Tabor and Hermon shall rejoice in thy name.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast a mighty arm: strong is thy hand, and high is thy right hand.
verses.verse_html:
13Thou hast a mighty arm: strong is thy hand, and high is thy right hand. ▼
▼ a…: Heb. an arm with might

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a…: Heb. an arm with might
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a…: Heb. an arm with might

verses.text_plain: Justice and judgment are the habitation of thy throne: mercy and truth shall go before thy face.
verses.verse_html:
14Justice and judgment are the habitation of thy throne: mercy and truth shall go before thy face. ▼
▼ habitation: or, establishment

verses.text_plain: Blessed is the people that know the joyful sound: they shall walk, O Lord, in the light of thy countenance.
verses.verse_html: 15Blessed is the people that know the joyful sound: they shall walk, O Lord, in the light of thy countenance.

verses.text_plain: In thy name shall they rejoice all the day: and in thy righteousness shall they be exalted.
verses.verse_html: 16In thy name shall they rejoice all the day: and in thy righteousness shall they be exalted.

verses.text_plain: For thou art the glory of their strength: and in thy favour our horn shall be exalted.
verses.verse_html: 17For thou art the glory of their strength: and in thy favour our horn shall be exalted.

verses.text_plain: For the Lord is our defence; and the Holy One of Israel is our king.
verses.verse_html:
18For the Lord is our defence; and the Holy One of Israel is our king. ▼
▼ the Lord…: or, our shield is of the Lord, and our king is of the Holy One of Israel

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the Lord…: or, our shield is of the Lord, and our king is of the Holy One of Israel
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the Lord…: or, our shield is of the Lord, and our king is of the Holy One of Israel

verses.text_plain: Then thou spakest in vision to thy holy one, and saidst, I have laid help upon one that is mighty; I have exalted one chosen out of the people.
verses.verse_html: 19Then thou spakest in vision to thy holy one, and saidst, I have laid help upon one that is mighty; I have exalted one chosen out of the people.

verses.text_plain: I have found David my servant; with my holy oil have I anointed him:
verses.verse_html: 20I have found David my servant; with my holy oil have I anointed him:

verses.text_plain: With whom my hand shall be established: mine arm also shall strengthen him.
verses.verse_html: 21With whom my hand shall be established: mine arm also shall strengthen him.

verses.text_plain: The enemy shall not exact upon him; nor the son of wickedness afflict him.
verses.verse_html: 22The enemy shall not exact upon him; nor the son of wickedness afflict him.

verses.text_plain: And I will beat down his foes before his face, and plague them that hate him.
verses.verse_html: 23And I will beat down his foes before his face, and plague them that hate him.

verses.text_plain: But my faithfulness and my mercy shall be with him: and in my name shall his horn be exalted.
verses.verse_html: 24But my faithfulness and my mercy shall be with him: and in my name shall his horn be exalted.

tokens.text: with him: and in my name

verses.text_plain: I will set his hand also in the sea, and his right hand in the rivers.
verses.verse_html: 25I will set his hand also in the sea, and his right hand in the rivers.

verses.text_plain: He shall cry unto me, Thou art my father, my God, and the rock of my salvation.
verses.verse_html: 26He shall cry unto me, Thou art my father, my God, and the rock of my salvation.

verses.text_plain: Also I will make him my firstborn, higher than the kings of the earth.
verses.verse_html: 27Also I will make him my firstborn, higher than the kings of the earth.

verses.text_plain: My mercy will I keep for him for evermore, and my covenant shall stand fast with him.
verses.verse_html: 28My mercy will I keep for him for evermore, and my covenant shall stand fast with him.

verses.text_plain: His seed also will I make to endure for ever, and his throne as the days of heaven.
verses.verse_html: 29His seed also will I make to endure for ever, and his throne as the days of heaven.

verses.text_plain: If his children forsake my law, and walk not in my judgments;
verses.verse_html: 30If his children forsake my law, and walk not in my judgments;

verses.text_plain: If they break my statutes, and keep not my commandments;
verses.verse_html:
31If they break my statutes, and keep not my commandments; ▼
▼ break: Heb. profane

verses.text_plain: Then will I visit their transgression with the rod, and their iniquity with stripes.
verses.verse_html: 32Then will I visit their transgression with the rod, and their iniquity with stripes.

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless my lovingkindness will I not utterly take from him, nor suffer my faithfulness to fail.
verses.verse_html:
33Nevertheless my lovingkindness will I not utterly take from him, nor suffer my faithfulness to fail. ▼
▼ will…: Heb. I will not make void from him
 , ▼
▼ to fail: Heb. to lie

tokens.text: from him, nor suffer my faithfulness

footnotes.body_text: ▼ will…: Heb. I will not make void from him
footnotes.body_html: ▼ will…: Heb. I will not make void from him
▼ to fail: Heb. to lie

verses.text_plain: My covenant will I not break, nor alter the thing that is gone out of my lips.
verses.verse_html: 34My covenant will I not break, nor alter the thing that is gone out of my lips.

tokens.text: the thing that is gone out

verses.text_plain: Once have I sworn by my holiness that I will not lie unto David.
verses.verse_html:
35Once have I sworn by my holiness that I will not lie unto David. ▼
▼ that…: Heb. if I lie

footnotes.body_html: ▼ that…: Heb. if I lie

verses.text_plain: His seed shall endure for ever, and his throne as the sun before me.
verses.verse_html: 36His seed shall endure for ever, and his throne as the sun before me.

verses.text_plain: It shall be established for ever as the moon, and as a faithful witness in heaven. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 37It shall be established for ever as the moon, and as a faithful witness in heaven. Selah.

verses.text_plain: But thou hast cast off and abhorred, thou hast been wroth with thine anointed.
verses.verse_html: 38But thou hast cast off and abhorred, thou hast been wroth with thine anointed.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast made void the covenant of thy servant: thou hast profaned his crown by casting it to the ground.
verses.verse_html: 39Thou hast made void the covenant of thy servant: thou hast profaned his crown by casting it to the ground.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast broken down all his hedges; thou hast brought his strong holds to ruin.
verses.verse_html: 40Thou hast broken down all his hedges; thou hast brought his strong holds to ruin.

verses.text_plain: All that pass by the way spoil him: he is a reproach to his neighbours.
verses.verse_html: 41All that pass by the way spoil him: he is a reproach to his neighbours.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast set up the right hand of his adversaries; thou hast made all his enemies to rejoice.
verses.verse_html: 42Thou hast set up the right hand of his adversaries; thou hast made all his enemies to rejoice.

tokens.text: thou hast made all his enemies

verses.text_plain: Thou hast also turned the edge of his sword, and hast not made him to stand in the battle.
verses.verse_html: 43Thou hast also turned the edge of his sword, and hast not made him to stand in the battle.

tokens.text: and hast not made him to stand

verses.text_plain: Thou hast made his glory to cease, and cast his throne down to the ground.
verses.verse_html:
44Thou hast made his glory to cease, and cast his throne down to the ground. ▼
▼ glory: Heb. brightness

verses.text_plain: The days of his youth hast thou shortened: thou hast covered him with shame. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 45The days of his youth hast thou shortened: thou hast covered him with shame. Selah.

verses.text_plain: How long, Lord? wilt thou hide thyself for ever? shall thy wrath burn like fire?
verses.verse_html: 46How long, Lord? wilt thou hide thyself for ever? shall thy wrath burn like fire?

verses.text_plain: Remember how short my time is: wherefore hast thou made all men in vain?
verses.verse_html: 47Remember how short my time is: wherefore hast thou made all men in vain?

tokens.text: my time is: wherefore hast thou made

verses.text_plain: What man is he that liveth, and shall not see death? shall he deliver his soul from the hand of the grave? Selah.
verses.verse_html: 48What man is he that liveth, and shall not see death? shall he deliver his soul from the hand of the grave? Selah.

verses.text_plain: Lord, where are thy former lovingkindnesses, which thou swarest unto David in thy truth?
verses.verse_html: 49Lord, where are thy former lovingkindnesses, which thou swarest unto David in thy truth?

verses.text_plain: Remember, Lord, the reproach of thy servants; how I do bear in my bosom the reproach of all the mighty people;
verses.verse_html: 50Remember, Lord, the reproach of thy servants; how I do bear in my bosom the reproach of all the mighty people;

verses.text_plain: Wherewith thine enemies have reproached, O Lord; wherewith they have reproached the footsteps of thine anointed.
verses.verse_html: 51Wherewith thine enemies have reproached, O Lord; wherewith they have reproached the footsteps of thine anointed.

verses.text_plain: Blessed be the Lord for evermore. Amen, and Amen.
verses.verse_html: 52Blessed be the Lord for evermore. Amen, and Amen.
